The desired behavior of [freeNSynapses](https://github.com/numenta/nupic.core/blob/master/src/nupic/algorithms/Segment.cpp#L346) is to delete synapses with the lowest permanences first from the set of inactive synapses, and then if there are insufficiently many inactive synapse, from the active synapses, until the requested number of synapses has been deleted. Deleting synapses with low permanence has the least possible effect on the algorithm's outcome.

However, the current implementation is broken in that it does not correctly associate the index of the synapse with its permanence. **Thus arbitrary synapses are deleted.** In particular, [this loop](https://github.com/numenta/nupic.core/blob/master/src/nupic/algorithms/Segment.cpp#L371-L377) that currently reads

```C++
  InSynapses candidates;
  for (UInt i = 0; i < inactiveSegmentIndices.size(); i++)
  {
    // Put in *segment indices*, not source cell indices
    candidates.push_back(InSynapse(inactiveSegmentIndices[i],
                                   _synapses[i].permanence()));
  }
```
should instead read

```C++
InSynapses candidates;
for (UInt i = 0; i < inactiveSegmentIndices.size(); i++)
{
  // Put in *segment indices*, not source cell indices
  candidates.push_back(InSynapse(inactiveSegmentIndices[i],
                                _synapses[inactiveSegmentIndices[i]].permanence()));
}
```

and a similar modification should be made for the [second loop](https://github.com/numenta/nupic.core/blob/master/src/nupic/algorithms/Segment.cpp#L382-L389).

There are currently no unit tests for `freeNSynapses`, and making the above modification does not cause any of the existing nupic.core unit or integration tests to fail.

