@jen20 wrote a program that led to a component resource having an empty parent property. This should never happen, since we default to the "root" `pulumi:pulumi:Stack` resource. I vaguely recall an old bug we had where if a resource got created too late, we had already reset the global root resource object, due to the way the root resource is managed. This looks fine, however

https://github.com/pulumi/pulumi/blob/48aa5e73f82b6635d0f236ffcd98e77e705a99c3/sdk/nodejs/runtime/stack.ts#L42-L50

but perhaps there's something else going on here. I wonder if it could be something about multiple `@pulumi/pulumi` modules getting loaded into memory?
